						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">JoeGtake2 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Also, would you suggest an emulator that supports mapper 30 that might be a good second-check?  I have a lot of other emus, but none that support mapper 30, which is why I've relied on a thing Shiru built for us for SUPER birds eye view quick proto, FCEUX to get closer and debug, and then hardware as a final look.  It might be good to have another intermediary.<br /></div>Mapper 30 is just UNROM with 2 additional optional things:<br />1- CHR-RAM bankswitching<br />2- self-flash capability<br /><br />Caitsith2 had added support to FCEUX as of april 2014, so modern releases should have it...<br />Mesen doesn't have self-flashing but does support CHR-RAM bankswitching.<br />I don't think the previous generation of best-in-breed emulators are supported enough to have it.<br /><br />But if you're not relying on those two behaviors, you should be able to just run it as mapper 2 for testing.</div>

					
